Net Time In Zone measures something crucial: not how long you trained, but what intensity you actually spent time at. It's the difference between watching the clock and understanding your true training dose.

Think of a 90-minute workout as a container. NTIZ tells us what's inside that container—maybe 55 minutes of easy Zone 1 cruising, 30 minutes of hard Zone 3 tempo work, and five minutes of transitions that don't count.

